The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Asnani to replace Benson 
                                                   Asnani to replace Benson 
            OUR CORRESPONDENT                      
	Nagpur: Mark Benson, who couldnt officiate in the opening one-dayer in Vadodara because of a severe bout of migraine, was Tuesday admitted to a hospital here.         
	Benson hasnt recovered from the illness and we decided to get him admitted for a thorough checkup He is stable, a Vidarbha Cricket Association official said.         
	Sudhir Asnani will take Bensons place and would be the on-field umpire with Amiesh Saheba on Wednesday. S.K. Tarapore, who stood for a sick Benson in Vadodara, would be the third umpire.         
	Benson, the ICC Elite panel umpire, had also taken ill during the India-South Africa Test in Durban almost three years ago.         
	Hed been rushed to hospital from Kingsmead, and soon afterwards, underwent a heart surgery.                                                                                                                       
